- creating test
    1. create a font
    2. write text on surface
    3. blit the text surface

- text type can be mod by import .ttf files

- import img.convert() or convert_alpha() will reformat png into something that pygame can work better with

- rectangles
    1. precise placement of img
        1.1 surface for image information
        2.2 placement via rectangle

- to avoid multiple collision detections, can use invincibility frame

- pg.mouse.get_pressed() will return a tuple of 3 boolean vars, representing lef, mid, and right button of the mouse
    - For example, if right click, will return (False, False, True)